            "text": "// Released under MIT license\n// Copyright (c) 2009-2010 Dominic Baggott\n// Copyright (c) 2009-2010 Ash Berlin\n// Copyright (c) 2011 Christoph Dorn <christoph@christophdorn.com> (http://www.christophdorn.com)\n\n/*jshint browser:true, devel:true */\n\n(function( expose ) {\n\n/**\n *  class Markdown\n *\n *  Markdown processing in Javascript done right. We have very particular views\n *  on what constitutes 'right' which include:\n *\n *  - produces well-formed HTML (this means that em and strong nesting is\n *    important)\n *\n *  - has an intermediate representation to allow processing of parsed data (We\n *    in fact have two, both as [JsonML]: a markdown tree and an HTML tree).\n *\n *  - is easily extensible to add new dialects without having to rewrite the\n *    entire parsing mechanics\n *\n *  - has a good test suite\n *\n *  This implementation fulfills all of these (except that the test suite could\n *  do with expanding to automatically run all the fixtures from other Markdown\n *  implementations.)\n *\n *  ##### Intermediate Representation\n *\n *  *TODO* Talk about this :) Its JsonML, but document the node names we use.\n *\n *  [JsonML]: http://jsonml.org/ \"JSON Markup Language\"\n **/\nvar Markdown = expose.Markdown = function(dialect) {\n  switch (typeof dialect) {\n    case \"undefined\":\n      this.dialect = Markdown.dialects.Gruber;\n      break;\n    case \"object\":\n      this.dialect = dialect;\n      break;\n    default:\n      if ( dialect in Markdown.dialects ) {\n        this.dialect = Markdown.dialects[dialect];\n      }\n      else {\n        throw new Error(\"Unknown Markdown dialect '\" + String(dialect) + \"'\");\n      }\n      break;\n  }\n  this.em_state = [];\n  this.strong_state = [];\n  this.debug_indent = \"\";\n};\n\n/**\n *  parse( markdown, [dialect] ) -> JsonML\n *  - markdown (String): markdown string to parse\n *  - dialect (String | Dialect): the dialect to use, defaults to gruber\n *\n *  Parse `markdown` and return a markdown document as a Markdown.JsonML tree.\n **/\nexpose.parse = function( source, dialect ) {\n  // dialect will default if undefined\n  var md = new Markdown( dialect );\n  return md.toTree( source );\n};\n\n/**\n *  toHTML( markdown, [dialect]  ) -> String\n *  toHTML( md_tree ) -> String\n *  - markdown (String): markdown string to parse\n *  - md_tree (Markdown.JsonML): parsed markdown tree\n *\n *  Take markdown (either as a string or as a JsonML tree) and run it through\n *  [[toHTMLTree]] then turn it into a well-formated HTML fragment.\n **/\nexpose.toHTML = function toHTML( source , dialect , options ) {\n  var input = expose.toHTMLTree( source , dialect , options );\n\n  return expose.renderJsonML( input );\n};\n\n/**\n *  toHTMLTree( markdown, [dialect] ) -> JsonML\n *  toHTMLTree( md_tree ) -> JsonML\n *  - markdown (String): markdown string to parse\n *  - dialect (String | Dialect): the dialect to use, defaults to gruber\n *  - md_tree (Markdown.JsonML): parsed markdown tree\n *\n *  Turn markdown into HTML, represented as a JsonML tree. If a string is given\n *  to this function, it is first parsed into a markdown tree by calling\n *  [[parse]].\n **/\nexpose.toHTMLTree = function toHTMLTree( input, dialect , options ) {\n  // convert string input to an MD tree\n  if ( typeof input ===\"string\" ) input = this.parse( input, dialect );\n\n  // Now convert the MD tree to an HTML tree\n\n  // remove references from the tree\n  var attrs = extract_attr( input ),\n      refs = {};\n\n  if ( attrs && attrs.references ) {\n    refs = attrs.references;\n  }\n\n  var html = convert_tree_to_html( input, refs , options );\n  merge_text_nodes( html );\n  return html;\n};\n\n// For Spidermonkey based engines\nfunction mk_block_toSource() {\n  return \"Markdown.mk_block( \" +\n          uneval(this.toString()) +\n          \", \" +\n          uneval(this.trailing) +\n          \", \" +\n          uneval(this.lineNumber) +\n          \" )\";\n}\n\n// node\nfunction mk_block_inspect() {\n  var util = require(\"util\");\n  return \"Markdown.mk_block( \" +\n          util.inspect(this.toString()) +\n          \", \" +\n          util.inspect(this.trailing) +\n          \", \" +\n          util.inspect(this.lineNumber) +\n          \" )\";\n\n}\n\nvar mk_block = Markdown.mk_block = function(block, trail, line) {\n  // Be helpful for default case in tests.\n  if ( arguments.length == 1 ) trail = \"\\n\\n\";\n\n  var s = new String(block);\n  s.trailing = trail;\n  // To make it clear its not just a string\n  s.inspect = mk_block_inspect;\n  s.toSource = mk_block_toSource;\n\n  if ( line != undefined )\n    s.lineNumber = line;\n\n  return s;\n};\n\nfunction count_lines( str ) {\n  var n = 0, i = -1;\n  while ( ( i = str.indexOf(\"\\n\", i + 1) ) !== -1 ) n++;\n  return n;\n}\n\n// Internal - split source into rough blocks\nMarkdown.prototype.split_blocks = function splitBlocks( input, startLine ) {\n  input = input.replace(/(\\r\\n|\\n|\\r)/g, \"\\n\");\n  // [\\s\\S] matches _anything_ (newline or space)\n  // [^] is equivalent but doesn't work in IEs.\n  var re = /([\\s\\S]+?)($|\\n#|\\n(?:\\s*\\n|$)+)/g,\n      blocks = [],\n      m;\n\n  var line_no = 1;\n\n  if ( ( m = /^(\\s*\\n)/.exec(input) ) != null ) {\n    // skip (but count) leading blank lines\n    line_no += count_lines( m[0] );\n    re.lastIndex = m[0].length;\n  }\n\n  while ( ( m = re.exec(input) ) !== null ) {\n    if (m[2] == \"\\n#\") {\n      m[2] = \"\\n\";\n      re.lastIndex--;\n    }\n    blocks.push( mk_block( m[1], m[2], line_no ) );\n    line_no += count_lines( m[0] );\n  }\n\n  return blocks;\n};\n\n/**\n *  Markdown#processBlock( block, next ) -> undefined | [ JsonML, ... ]\n *  - block (String): the block to process\n *  - next (Array): the following blocks\n *\n * Process `block` and return an array of JsonML nodes representing `block`.\n *\n * It does this by asking each block level function in the dialect to process\n * the block until one can. Succesful handling is indicated by returning an\n * array (with zero or more JsonML nodes), failure by a false value.\n *\n * Blocks handlers are responsible for calling [[Markdown#processInline]]\n * themselves as appropriate.\n *\n * If the blocks were split incorrectly or adjacent blocks need collapsing you\n * can adjust `next` in place using shift/splice etc.\n *\n * If any of this default behaviour is not right for the dialect, you can\n * define a `__call__` method on the dialect that will get invoked to handle\n * the block processing.\n */\nMarkdown.prototype.processBlock = function processBlock( block, next ) {\n  var cbs = this.dialect.block,\n      ord = cbs.__order__;\n\n  if ( \"__call__\" in cbs ) {\n    return cbs.__call__.call(this, block, next);\n  }\n\n  for ( var i = 0; i < ord.length; i++ ) {\n    //D:this.debug( \"Testing\", ord[i] );\n    var res = cbs[ ord[i] ].call( this, block, next );\n    if ( res ) {\n      //D:this.debug(\"  matched\");\n      if ( !isArray(res) || ( res.length > 0 && !( isArray(res[0]) ) ) )\n        this.debug(ord[i], \"didn't return a proper array\");\n      //D:this.debug( \"\" );\n      return res;\n    }\n  }\n\n  // Uhoh! no match! Should we throw an error?\n  return [];\n};\n\nMarkdown.prototype.processInline = function processInline( block ) {\n  return this.dialect.inline.__call__.call( this, String( block ) );\n};\n\n/**\n *  Markdown#toTree( source ) -> JsonML\n *  - source (String): markdown source to parse\n *\n *  Parse `source` into a JsonML tree representing the markdown document.\n **/\n// custom_tree means set this.tree to `custom_tree` and restore old value on return\nMarkdown.prototype.toTree = function toTree( source, custom_root ) {\n  var blocks = source instanceof Array ? source : this.split_blocks( source );\n\n  // Make tree a member variable so its easier to mess with in extensions\n  var old_tree = this.tree;\n  try {\n    this.tree = custom_root || this.tree || [ \"markdown\" ];\n\n    blocks:\n    while ( blocks.length ) {\n      var b = this.processBlock( blocks.shift(), blocks );\n\n      // Reference blocks and the like won't return any content\n      if ( !b.length ) continue blocks;\n\n      this.tree.push.apply( this.tree, b );\n    }\n    return this.tree;\n  }\n  finally {\n    if ( custom_root ) {\n      this.tree = old_tree;\n    }\n  }\n};\n\n// Noop by default\nMarkdown.prototype.debug = function () {\n  var args = Array.prototype.slice.call( arguments);\n  args.unshift(this.debug_indent);\n  if ( typeof print !== \"undefined\" )\n      print.apply( print, args );\n  if ( typeof console !== \"undefined\" && typeof console.log !== \"undefined\" )\n      console.log.apply( null, args );\n}\n\nMarkdown.prototype.loop_re_over_block = function( re, block, cb ) {\n  // Dont use /g regexps with this\n  var m,\n      b = block.valueOf();\n\n  while ( b.length && (m = re.exec(b) ) != null ) {\n    b = b.substr( m[0].length );\n    cb.call(this, m);\n  }\n  return b;\n};\n\n/**\n * Markdown.dialects\n *\n * Namespace of built-in dialects.\n **/\nMarkdown.dialects = {};\n\n/**\n * Markdown.dialects.Gruber\n *\n * The default dialect that follows the rules set out by John Gruber's\n * markdown.pl as closely as possible. Well actually we follow the behaviour of\n * that script which in some places is not exactly what the syntax web page\n * says.\n **/\nMarkdown.dialects.Gruber = {\n  block: {\n    atxHeader: function atxHeader( block, next ) {\n      var m = block.match( /^(#{1,6})\\s*(.*?)\\s*#*\\s*(?:\\n|$)/ );\n\n      if ( !m ) return undefined;\n\n      var header = [ \"header\", { level: m[ 1 ].length } ];\n      Array.prototype.push.apply(header, this.processInline(m[ 2 ]));\n\n      if ( m[0].length < block.length )\n        next.unshift( mk_block( block.substr( m[0].length ), block.trailing, block.lineNumber + 2 ) );\n\n      return [ header ];\n    },\n\n    setextHeader: function setextHeader( block, next ) {\n      var m = block.match( /^(.*)\\n([-=])\\2\\2+(?:\\n|$)/ );\n\n      if ( !m ) return undefined;\n\n      var level = ( m[ 2 ] === \"=\" ) ? 1 : 2;\n      var header = [ \"header\", { level : level }, m[ 1 ] ];\n\n      if ( m[0].length < block.length )\n        next.unshift( mk_block( block.substr( m[0].length ), block.trailing, block.lineNumber + 2 ) );\n\n      return [ header ];\n    },\n\n    code: function code( block, next ) {\n      // |    Foo\n      // |bar\n      // should be a code block followed by a paragraph. Fun\n      //\n      // There might also be adjacent code block to merge.\n\n      var ret = [],\n          re = /^(?: {0,3}\\t| {4})(.*)\\n?/,\n          lines;\n\n      // 4 spaces + content\n      if ( !block.match( re ) ) return undefined;\n\n      block_search:\n      do {\n        // Now pull out the rest of the lines\n        var b = this.loop_re_over_block(\n                  re, block.valueOf(), function( m ) { ret.push( m[1] ); } );\n\n        if ( b.length ) {\n          // Case alluded to in first comment. push it back on as a new block\n          next.unshift( mk_block(b, block.trailing) );\n          break block_search;\n        }\n        else if ( next.length ) {\n          // Check the next block - it might be code too\n          if ( !next[0].match( re ) ) break block_search;\n\n          // Pull how how many blanks lines follow - minus two to account for .join\n          ret.push ( block.trailing.replace(/[^\\n]/g, \"\").substring(2) );\n\n          block = next.shift();\n        }\n        else {\n          break block_search;\n        }\n      } while ( true );\n\n      return [ [ \"code_block\", ret.join(\"\\n\") ] ];\n    },\n\n    horizRule: function horizRule( block, next ) {\n      // this needs to find any hr in the block to handle abutting blocks\n      var m = block.match( /^(?:([\\s\\S]*?)\\n)?[ \\t]*([-_*])(?:[ \\t]*\\2){2,}[ \\t]*(?:\\n([\\s\\S]*))?$/ );\n\n      if ( !m ) {\n        return undefined;\n      }\n\n      var jsonml = [ [ \"hr\" ] ];\n\n      // if there's a leading abutting block, process it\n      if ( m[ 1 ] ) {\n        jsonml.unshift.apply( jsonml, this.processBlock( m[ 1 ], [] ) );\n      }\n\n      // if there's a trailing abutting block, stick it into next\n      if ( m[ 3 ] ) {\n        next.unshift( mk_block( m[ 3 ] ) );\n      }\n\n      return jsonml;\n    },\n\n    // There are two types of lists. Tight and loose. Tight lists have no whitespace\n    // between the items (and result in text just in the <li>) and loose lists,\n    // which have an empty line between list items, resulting in (one or more)\n    // paragraphs inside the <li>.\n    //\n    // There are all sorts weird edge cases about the original markdown.pl's\n    // handling of lists:\n    //\n    // * Nested lists are supposed to be indented by four chars per level. But\n    //   if they aren't, you can get a nested list by indenting by less than\n    //   four so long as the indent doesn't match an indent of an existing list\n    //   item in the 'nest stack'.\n    //\n    // * The type of the list (bullet or number) is controlled just by the\n    //    first item at the indent. Subsequent changes are ignored unless they\n    //    are for nested lists\n    //\n    lists: (function( ) {\n      // Use a closure to hide a few variables.\n      var any_list = \"[*+-]|\\\\d+\\\\.\",\n          bullet_list = /[*+-]/,\n          number_list = /\\d+\\./,\n          // Capture leading indent as it matters for determining nested lists.\n          is_list_re = new RegExp( \"^( {0,3})(\" + any_list + \")[ \\t]+\" ),\n          indent_re = \"(?: {0,3}\\\\t| {4})\";\n\n      // TODO: Cache this regexp for certain depths.\n      // Create a regexp suitable for matching an li for a given stack depth\n      function regex_for_depth( depth ) {\n\n        return new RegExp(\n          // m[1] = indent, m[2] = list_type\n          \"(?:^(\" + indent_re + \"{0,\" + depth + \"} {0,3})(\" + any_list + \")\\\\s+)|\" +\n          // m[3] = cont\n          \"(^\" + indent_re + \"{0,\" + (depth-1) + \"}[ ]{0,4})\"\n        );\n      }\n      function expand_tab( input ) {\n        return input.replace( / {0,3}\\t/g, \"    \" );\n      }\n\n      // Add inline content `inline` to `li`. inline comes from processInline\n      // so is an array of content\n      function add(li, loose, inline, nl) {\n        if ( loose ) {\n          li.push( [ \"para\" ].concat(inline) );\n          return;\n        }\n        // Hmmm, should this be any block level element or just paras?\n        var add_to = li[li.length -1] instanceof Array && li[li.length - 1][0] == \"para\"\n                   ? li[li.length -1]\n                   : li;\n\n        // If there is already some content in this list, add the new line in\n        if ( nl && li.length > 1 ) inline.unshift(nl);\n\n        for ( var i = 0; i < inline.length; i++ ) {\n          var what = inline[i],\n              is_str = typeof what == \"string\";\n          if ( is_str && add_to.length > 1 && typeof add_to[add_to.length-1] == \"string\" ) {\n            add_to[ add_to.length-1 ] += what;\n          }\n          else {\n            add_to.push( what );\n          }\n        }\n      }\n\n      // contained means have an indent greater than the current one. On\n      // *every* line in the block\n      function get_contained_blocks( depth, blocks ) {\n\n        var re = new RegExp( \"^(\" + indent_re + \"{\" + depth + \"}.*?\\\\n?)*$\" ),\n            replace = new RegExp(\"^\" + indent_re + \"{\" + depth + \"}\", \"gm\"),\n            ret = [];\n\n        while ( blocks.length > 0 ) {\n          if ( re.exec( blocks[0] ) ) {\n            var b = blocks.shift(),\n                // Now remove that indent\n                x = b.replace( replace, \"\");\n\n            ret.push( mk_block( x, b.trailing, b.lineNumber ) );\n          }\n          else {\n            break;\n          }\n        }\n        return ret;\n      }\n\n      // passed to stack.forEach to turn list items up the stack into paras\n      function paragraphify(s, i, stack) {\n        var list = s.list;\n        var last_li = list[list.length-1];\n\n        if ( last_li[1] instanceof Array && last_li[1][0] == \"para\" ) {\n          return;\n        }\n        if ( i + 1 == stack.length ) {\n          // Last stack frame\n          // Keep the same array, but replace the contents\n          last_li.push( [\"para\"].concat( last_li.splice(1, last_li.length - 1) ) );\n        }\n        else {\n          var sublist = last_li.pop();\n          last_li.push( [\"para\"].concat( last_li.splice(1, last_li.length - 1) ), sublist );\n        }\n      }\n\n      // The matcher function\n      return function( block, next ) {\n        var m = block.match( is_list_re );\n        if ( !m ) return undefined;\n\n        function make_list( m ) {\n          var list = bullet_list.exec( m[2] )\n                   ? [\"bulletlist\"]\n                   : [\"numberlist\"];\n\n          stack.push( { list: list, indent: m[1] } );\n          return list;\n        }\n\n\n        var stack = [], // Stack of lists for nesting.\n            list = make_list( m ),\n            last_li,\n            loose = false,\n            ret = [ stack[0].list ],\n            i;\n\n        // Loop to search over block looking for inner block elements and loose lists\n        loose_search:\n        while ( true ) {\n          // Split into lines preserving new lines at end of line\n          var lines = block.split( /(?=\\n)/ );\n\n          // We have to grab all lines for a li and call processInline on them\n          // once as there are some inline things that can span lines.\n          var li_accumulate = \"\";\n\n          // Loop over the lines in this block looking for tight lists.\n          tight_search:\n          for ( var line_no = 0; line_no < lines.length; line_no++ ) {\n            var nl = \"\",\n                l = lines[line_no].replace(/^\\n/, function(n) { nl = n; return \"\"; });\n\n            // TODO: really should cache this\n            var line_re = regex_for_depth( stack.length );\n\n            m = l.match( line_re );\n            //print( \"line:\", uneval(l), \"\\nline match:\", uneval(m) );\n\n            // We have a list item\n            if ( m[1] !== undefined ) {\n              // Process the previous list item, if any\n              if ( li_accumulate.length ) {\n                add( last_li, loose, this.processInline( li_accumulate ), nl );\n                // Loose mode will have been dealt with. Reset it\n                loose = false;\n                li_accumulate = \"\";\n              }\n\n              m[1] = expand_tab( m[1] );\n              var wanted_depth = Math.floor(m[1].length/4)+1;\n              //print( \"want:\", wanted_depth, \"stack:\", stack.length);\n              if ( wanted_depth > stack.length ) {\n                // Deep enough for a nested list outright\n                //print ( \"new nested list\" );\n                list = make_list( m );\n                last_li.push( list );\n                last_li = list[1] = [ \"listitem\" ];\n              }\n              else {\n                // We aren't deep enough to be strictly a new level. This is\n                // where Md.pl goes nuts. If the indent matches a level in the\n                // stack, put it there, else put it one deeper then the\n                // wanted_depth deserves.\n                var found = false;\n                for ( i = 0; i < stack.length; i++ ) {\n                  if ( stack[ i ].indent != m[1] ) continue;\n                  list = stack[ i ].list;\n                  stack.splice( i+1, stack.length - (i+1) );\n                  found = true;\n                  break;\n                }\n\n                if (!found) {\n                  //print(\"not found. l:\", uneval(l));\n                  wanted_depth++;\n                  if ( wanted_depth <= stack.length ) {\n                    stack.splice(wanted_depth, stack.length - wanted_depth);\n                    //print(\"Desired depth now\", wanted_depth, \"stack:\", stack.length);\n                    list = stack[wanted_depth-1].list;\n                    //print(\"list:\", uneval(list) );\n                  }\n                  else {\n                    //print (\"made new stack for messy indent\");\n                    list = make_list(m);\n                    last_li.push(list);\n                  }\n                }\n\n                //print( uneval(list), \"last\", list === stack[stack.length-1].list );\n                last_li = [ \"listitem\" ];\n                list.push(last_li);\n              } // end depth of shenegains\n              nl = \"\";\n            }\n\n            // Add content\n            if ( l.length > m[0].length ) {\n              li_accumulate += nl + l.substr( m[0].length );\n            }\n          } // tight_search\n\n          if ( li_accumulate.length ) {\n            add( last_li, loose, this.processInline( li_accumulate ), nl );\n            // Loose mode will have been dealt with. Reset it\n            loose = false;\n            li_accumulate = \"\";\n          }\n\n          // Look at the next block - we might have a loose list. Or an extra\n          // paragraph for the current li\n          var contained = get_contained_blocks( stack.length, next );\n\n          // Deal with code blocks or properly nested lists\n          if ( contained.length > 0 ) {\n            // Make sure all listitems up the stack are paragraphs\n            forEach( stack, paragraphify, this);\n\n            last_li.push.apply( last_li, this.toTree( contained, [] ) );\n          }\n\n          var next_block = next[0] && next[0].valueOf() || \"\";\n\n          if ( next_block.match(is_list_re) || next_block.match( /^ / ) ) {\n            block = next.shift();\n\n            // Check for an HR following a list: features/lists/hr_abutting\n            var hr = this.dialect.block.horizRule( block, next );\n\n            if ( hr ) {\n              ret.push.apply(ret, hr);\n              break;\n            }\n\n            // Make sure all listitems up the stack are paragraphs\n            forEach( stack, paragraphify, this);\n\n            loose = true;\n            continue loose_search;\n          }\n          break;\n        } // loose_search\n\n        return ret;\n      };\n    })(),\n\n    blockquote: function blockquote( block, next ) {\n      if ( !block.match( /^>/m ) )\n        return undefined;\n\n      var jsonml = [];\n\n      // separate out the leading abutting block, if any. I.e. in this case:\n      //\n      //  a\n      //  > b\n      //\n      if ( block[ 0 ] != \">\" ) {\n        var lines = block.split( /\\n/ ),\n            prev = [],\n            line_no = block.lineNumber;\n\n        // keep shifting lines until you find a crotchet\n        while ( lines.length && lines[ 0 ][ 0 ] != \">\" ) {\n            prev.push( lines.shift() );\n            line_no++;\n        }\n\n        var abutting = mk_block( prev.join( \"\\n\" ), \"\\n\", block.lineNumber );\n        jsonml.push.apply( jsonml, this.processBlock( abutting, [] ) );\n        // reassemble new block of just block quotes!\n        block = mk_block( lines.join( \"\\n\" ), block.trailing, line_no );\n      }\n\n\n      // if the next block is also a blockquote merge it in\n      while ( next.length && next[ 0 ][ 0 ] == \">\" ) {\n        var b = next.shift();\n        block = mk_block( block + block.trailing + b, b.trailing, block.lineNumber );\n      }\n\n      // Strip off the leading \"> \" and re-process as a block.\n      var input = block.replace( /^> ?/gm, \"\" ),\n          old_tree = this.tree,\n          processedBlock = this.toTree( input, [ \"blockquote\" ] ),\n          attr = extract_attr( processedBlock );\n\n      // If any link references were found get rid of them\n      if ( attr && attr.references ) {\n        delete attr.references;\n        // And then remove the attribute object if it's empty\n        if ( isEmpty( attr ) ) {\n          processedBlock.splice( 1, 1 );\n        }\n      }\n\n      jsonml.push( processedBlock );\n      return jsonml;\n    },\n\n    referenceDefn: function referenceDefn( block, next) {\n      var re = /^\\s*\\[(.*?)\\]:\\s*(\\S+)(?:\\s+(?:(['\"])(.*?)\\3|\\((.*?)\\)))?\\n?/;\n      // interesting matches are [ , ref_id, url, , title, title ]\n\n      if ( !block.match(re) )\n        return undefined;\n\n      // make an attribute node if it doesn't exist\n      if ( !extract_attr( this.tree ) ) {\n        this.tree.splice( 1, 0, {} );\n      }\n\n      var attrs = extract_attr( this.tree );\n\n      // make a references hash if it doesn't exist\n      if ( attrs.references === undefined ) {\n        attrs.references = {};\n      }\n\n      var b = this.loop_re_over_block(re, block, function( m ) {\n\n        if ( m[2] && m[2][0] == \"<\" && m[2][m[2].length-1] == \">\" )\n          m[2] = m[2].substring( 1, m[2].length - 1 );\n\n        var ref = attrs.references[ m[1].toLowerCase() ] = {\n          href: m[2]\n        };\n\n        if ( m[4] !== undefined )\n          ref.title = basic case\n  if ( typeof jsonml === \"string\" ) {\n    return escapeHTML( jsonml );\n  }\n\n  var tag = jsonml.shift(),\n      attributes = {},\n      content = [];\n\n  if ( jsonml.length && typeof jsonml[ 0 ] === \"object\" && !( jsonml[ 0 ] instanceof Array ) ) {\n    attributes = jsonml.shift();\n  }\n\n  while ( jsonml.length ) {\n    content.push( render_tree( jsonml.shift() ) );\n  }\n\n  var tag_attrs = \"\";\n  for ( var a in attributes ) {\n    tag_attrs += \" \" + a + '=\"' + escapeHTML( attributes[ a ] ) + '\"';\n  }\n\n  // be careful about adding whitespace here for inline elements\n  if ( tag == \"img\" || tag == \"br\" || tag == \"hr\" ) {\n    return \"<\"+ tag + tag_attrs + \"/>\";\n  }\n  else {\n    return \"<\"+ tag + tag_attrs + \">\" + content.join( \"\" ) + \"</\" + tag + \">\";\n  }\n}\n\nfunction convert_tree_to_html( tree, references, options ) {\n  var i;\n  options = options || {};\n\n  // shallow clone\n  var jsonml = tree.slice( 0 );\n\n  if ( typeof options.preprocessTreeNode === \"function\" ) {\n      jsonml = options.preprocessTreeNode(jsonml, references);\n  }\n\n  // Clone attributes if they exist\n  var attrs = extract_attr( jsonml );\n  if ( attrs ) {\n    jsonml[ 1 ] = {};\n    for ( i in attrs ) {\n      jsonml[ 1 ][ i ] = attrs[ i ];\n    }\n    attrs = jsonml[ 1 ];\n  }\n\n  // basic case\n  if ( typeof jsonml === \"string\" ) {\n    return jsonml;\n  }\n\n  // convert this node\n  switch ( jsonml[ 0 ] ) {\n    case \"header\":\n      jsonml[ 0 ] = \"h\" + jsonml[ 1 ].level;\n      delete jsonml[ 1 ].level;\n      break;\n    case \"bulletlist\":\n      jsonml[ 0 ] = \"ul\";\n      break;\n    case \"numberlist\":\n      jsonml[ 0 ] = \"ol\";\n      break;\n    case \"listitem\":\n      jsonml[ 0 ] = \"li\";\n      break;\n    case \"para\":\n      jsonml[ 0 ] = \"p\";\n      break;\n    case \"markdown\":\n      jsonml[ 0 ] = \"html\";\n      if ( attrs ) delete attrs.references;\n      break;\n    case \"code_block\":\n      jsonml[ 0 ] = \"pre\";\n      i = attrs ? 2 : 1;\n      var code = [ \"code\" ];\n      code.push.apply( code, jsonml.splice( i, jsonml.length - i ) );\n      jsonml[ i ] = code;\n      break;\n    case \"inlinecode\":\n      jsonml[ 0 ] = \"code\";\n      break;\n    case \"img\":\n      jsonml[ 1 ].src = jsonml[ 1 ].href;\n      delete jsonml[ 1 ].href;\n      break;\n    case \"linebreak\":\n      jsonml[ 0 ] = \"br\";\n    break;\n    case \"link\":\n      jsonml[ 0 ] = \"a\";\n      break;\n    case \"link_ref\":\n      jsonml[ 0 ] = \"a\";\n\n      // grab this ref and clean up the attribute node\n      var ref = references[ attrs.ref ];\n\n      // if the reference exists, make the link\n      if ( ref ) {\n        delete attrs.ref;\n\n        // add in the href and title, if present\n        attrs.href = ref.href;\n        if ( ref.title ) {\n          attrs.title = ref.title;\n        }\n\n        // get rid of the unneeded original text\n        delete attrs.original;\n      }\n      // the reference doesn't exist, so revert to plain text\n      else {\n        return attrs.original;\n      }\n      break;\n    case \"img_ref\":\n      jsonml[ 0 ] = \"img\";\n\n      // grab this ref and clean up the attribute node\n      var ref = references[ attrs.ref ];\n\n      // if the reference exists, make the link\n      if ( ref ) {\n        delete attrs.ref;\n\n        // add in the href and title, if present\n        attrs.src = ref.href;\n        if ( ref.title ) {\n          attrs.title = ref.title;\n        }\n\n        // get rid of the unneeded original text\n        delete attrs.original;\n      }\n      // the reference doesn't exist, so revert to plain text\n      else {\n        return attrs.original;\n      }\n      break;\n  }\n\n  // convert all the children\n  i = 1;\n\n  // deal with the attribute node, if it exists\n  if ( attrs ) {\n    // if there are keys, skip over it\n    for ( var key in jsonml[ 1 ] ) {\n        i = 2;\n        break;\n    }\n    // if there aren't, remove it\n    if ( i === 1 ) {\n      jsonml.splice( i, 1 );\n    }\n  }\n\n  for ( ; i < jsonml.length; ++i ) {\n    jsonml[ i ] = convert_tree_to_html( jsonml[ i ], references, options );\n  }\n\n  return jsonml;\n}\n\n\n// merges adjacent text nodes into a single node\nfunction merge_text_nodes( jsonml ) {\n  // skip the tag name and attribute hash\n  var i = extract_attr( jsonml ) ? 2 : 1;\n\n  while ( i < jsonml.length ) {\n    // if it's a string check the next item too\n    if ( typeof jsonml[ i ] === \"string\" ) {\n      if ( i + 1 < jsonml.length && typeof jsonml[ i + 1 ] === \"string\" ) {\n        // merge the second string into the first and remove it\n        jsonml[ i ] += jsonml.splice( i + 1, 1 )[ 0 ];\n      }\n      else {\n        ++i;\n      }\n    }\n    // if it's not a string recurse\n    else {\n      merge_text_nodes( jsonml[ i ] );\n      ++i;\n    }\n  }\n}\n\n} )( (function() {\n  if ( typeof exports === \"undefined\" ) {\n    window.markdown = {};\n    return window.markdown;\n  }\n  else {\n    return exports;\n  }\n} )() );\n"

An extended dialect called \"Maruku\" is also included that provides table support and other advanced features. The syntax extensions are modelled on those of [[PHP Markdown Extra|https://michelf.ca/projects/php-markdown/extra/]].\n\nThe configuration tiddler [[$:/config/markdown/dialect]] determines which dialect is used:\n\n|!Dialect |!Description |\n|Gruber |Standard Markdown |\n|Maruku |Extended Maruku Markdown |\n\n\n! Creating ~WikiLinks\n\nCreate wiki links with the usual Markdown link syntax targeting `#` and the target tiddler title:\n\n```\n[link text](#TiddlerTitle)\n```\n\n! Images\n\nMarkdown image syntax can be used to reference images by tiddler title or an external URI. For example:\n\n```\n![alt text](/path/to/img.jpg \"Title\")\n\n![alt text](Motovun Jack.jpg \"Title\")\n```\n"

* Prevent modern browsers from displaying `audio` without controls.\n * Remove excess height in iOS 5 devices.\n */\n\naudio:not([controls]) {\n  display: none;\n  height: 0;\n}\n\n/**\n * Address ========================================================================== */\n\n/**\n * Remove the gray background color from active links in IE 10.\n */\n\na {\n  background: ========================================================================== */\n\n/**\n * Address styling not present in IE 8/9, Safari 5, and Chrome.\n */\n\nabbr[title] {\n  border-bottom: 1px */\n\ndfn {\n  font-style: italic;\n}\n\n/**\n * Address variable `h1` font-size and margin within `section` and `article`\n * contexts in Firefox 4+, Safari 5, and Chrome.\n */\n\nh1 {\n  font-size: 2em;\n  margin: 0.67em 0;\n}\n\n/**\n * Address styling not present in IE 8/9.\n */\n\nmark {\n  background: #ff0;\n  color: #000;\n}\n\n/**\n * Address inconsistent and variable font size in all browsers.\n */\n\nsmall {\n  font-size: 80%;\n}\n\n/**\n * Prevent `sub` and `sup` affecting `line-height` in all browsers.\n */\n\nsub,\nsup {\n  font-size: 75%;\n  line-height: 0;\n  position: */\n\ncode,\nkbd,\npre,\nsamp {\n  font-family: monospace, monospace;\n  font-size: 1em;\n}\n\n/* Forms\n   ========================================================================== */\n\n/**\n * Address margins set differently in Firefox 4+, Safari 5, and Chrome.\n */\n\nbutton,\ninput,\noptgroup,\nselect,\ntextarea {\n  color: inherit; /* 1 */\n  font: inherit; /* 2 */\n  margin: 0; /* 3 */\n}\n\n/**\n * Address `overflow` set to `hidden` in IE 8/9/10.\n */\n\nbutton {\n  overflow: visible;\n}\n\n/**\n * Address inconsistent `text-transform` inheritance for `button` and `select`.\n * All other form control elements do not inherit `text-transform` values.\n * Correct `button` style inheritance in Firefox, IE 8+, and Opera\n * Correct `select` style inheritance in Firefox.\n */\n\nbutton,\nselect {\n  text-transform: none;\n}\n\n/**\n * 1. Avoid the WebKit bug in Android 4.0.* where (2) destroys native `audio`\n *    and `video` controls.\n * 2. Correct inability to style clickable `input` types in iOS.\n * 3. Improve usability and consistency of cursor style between image-type\n *    `input` and others.\n */\n\nbutton,\nhtml input[type=\"button\"], /* 1 */\ninput[type=\"reset\"],\ninput[type=\"submit\"] {\n  -webkit-appearance: button; /* 2 */\n  cursor: pointer; /* 3 */\n}\n\n/**\n * Re-set default cursor for disabled elements.\n */\n\nbutton[disabled],\nhtml input[disabled] {\n  cursor: default;\n}\n\n/**\n * Remove inner padding and border in Firefox 4+.\n */\n\nbutton::-moz-focus-inner,\ninput::-moz-focus-inner {\n  border: 0;\n  padding: 0;\n}\n\n/**\n * Address Firefox 4+ setting `line-height` on `input` using `!important` in\n * the UA stylesheet.\n */\n\ninput {\n  line-height: normal;\n}\n\n/**\n * It's recommended that you don't attempt to style these elements.\n * Firefox's implementation doesn't respect box-sizing, padding, or width.\n *\n * 1. Address box sizing set to `content-box` in IE 8/9/10.\n * 2. Remove excess padding in IE 8/9/10.\n */\n\ninput[type=\"checkbox\"],\ninput[type=\"radio\"] {\n  box-sizing: border-box; /* 1 */\n  padding: 0; /* 2 */\n}\n\n/**\n * Fix the cursor style for Chrome's increment/decrement buttons. For certain\n * `font-size` values of the `input`, it causes the cursor style of the\n * decrement button to change from `default` to `text`.\n */\n\ninput[type=\"number\"]::-webkit-inner-spin-button,\ninput[type=\"number\"]::-webkit-outer-spin-button {\n  height: auto;\n}\n\n/**\n * 1. Address `appearance` set to `searchfield` in Safari 5 and Chrome.\n * 2. Address `box-sizing` set to `border-box` in Safari 5 and Chrome\n *    (include `-moz` to future-proof).\n */\n\ninput[type=\"search\"] {\n  -webkit-appearance: textfield; /* 1 */\n  -moz-box-sizing: content-box;\n  -webkit-box-sizing: content-box; /* 2 */\n  box-sizing: content-box;\n}\n\n/**\n * Remove inner padding and search cancel button in Safari and Chrome on OS X.\n * Safari (but not Chrome) clips the cancel button when the search input has\n * padding (and `textfield` appearance).\n */\n\ninput[type=\"search\"]::-webkit-search-cancel-button,\ninput[type=\"search\"]::-webkit-search-decoration {\n  -webkit-appearance: none;\n}\n\n/**\n * Define consistent border, margin, and padding.\n */\n\nfieldset {\n  border: 1px solid #c0c0c0;\n  margin: 0 2px;\n  padding: 0.35em 0.625em 0.75em;\n}\n\n/**\n * 1. Correct `color` not being inherited in IE 8/9.\n * 2. Remove padding so people aren't caught out if they zero out fieldsets.\n */\n\nlegend {\n  border: 0; /* 1 */\n  padding: 0; /* 2 */\n}\n\n/**\n * Remove default vertical scrollbar in IE 8/9.\n */\n\ntextarea {\n  overflow: auto;\n}\n\n/**\n * Don't inherit the `font-weight` (applied by a rule above).\n * NOTE: the default cannot safely be changed in Chrome and Safari on OS X.\n */\n\noptgroup {\n  font-weight: bold;\n}\n\n/* Tables\n   ========================================================================== */\n\n/**\n * Remove most spacing between table cells.\n */\n\ntable {\n  border-collapse: collapse;\n  border-spacing: 0;\n}\n\ntd,\nth {\n  padding: 0;\n}\n"
        },

!! 历史发展
最开始的时候GNU/linux只支持tar.gz,源代码编译安装模式,debian出现之后,人们认为需要有一种机制,用来管理计算机上的软件包,人们称为dpkg,后来redhat也着手建立自己的包管理系统rpm。接着很快陷入新的窘境,希望通过快捷高效的方式来安装软件包,所以出现了APT(Advanced Packaging Tool).

!! 源
```
main Canonical支持的开源软件
universe 社区维护的开源软件
restricted 设备的专有驱动
multiverse 有版权和合法限制的源
source 源代码
```

!! 样例
```
// 安装
sudo apt-get install libboost-all-dev
sudo apt-get install aptitude

// 卸载
// APT会把已装或已卸的软件都备份在硬盘上
apt-get remove packagename 保留配置文件
apt-get –purge remove packagename 删除配置文件
sudo apt-get autoclean 清理旧版本的软件缓存,清理掉已卸载的备份
sudo apt-get clean 清理所有软件缓存
sudo apt-get autoremove 删除系统不再使用的孤立软件

// 查询
apt-cache search string
aptitude search boost

// 查看包体之间的依赖关系
sudo apt-cache rdepends fonts-dejavu-extra
fonts-dejavu-extra
Reverse Depends:
  ttf-dejavu-extra
  fonts-dejavu

// 软件包
dpkg -L package 列出软件包中所有的文件
```












association Rule:关联规则
频繁项集
支持度
支持度阈值
候选项集
frequent Itemset:频繁项集
最大频繁项集


关联分析
关联规则


FP-growth Algorithm:FP增长算法







edu.yale.its.tp.cas.serviceTimeout:失效时间300






kerberos:基于windows域的sso
sso:single sign on 单点登录
saml:Security Assertion Markup Language 安全声明标记语言,2005年开始
Credentials:凭证
Web SSO:体现在客户端,为Web应用提供服务,对应的有桌面SSO
TGT:Ticket Granting Ticket
ST:Service Ticket,Web 客户端通过ST来访问服务,ST只能使用一次
PT:Proxy Ticket,代理Ticket
TGC:Ticket granting cookie->cas server 向用户发送的cookie 用户持有对自己身份信息的一种凭据
PGT:cas_client持有的代理用户的凭证
PGT URL:cas_server可以通过PGT_URL向用户提供PGT,表示一个代理服务






```
User:多个
Web应用:多个
SSO认证中心:1个,SSO认证中心通过一些方法告诉Web应用,当前访问用户
```

Web应用不处理User的登录,SSO认证中心和应用之间建立信任关系,认证中心的判断必须被应用信任

!background
在没有CAS之前,通过cookies来实现单点登录的

cas不应该使用http来登录,应该使用https来时间登录服务

! 背景
cas的架构模式,是基于web模式的cookie的,针对客户端模式的应用程序,集成单点登录.

http://denger.iteye.com/blog/973068

! 集成方式
* 通过restlet方式向cas server获取一个账户密码票据 TGT
* 通过票据获得对应应用服务的票据 ST
* 通过ST访问对应的应用系统
* 注销登陆票据 TGT

```
// 获取 TGT
curl -i -X POST -d "username=ysyh&password=111111" http://localhost:8082/cas/v1/tickets/

// 登录 ST
curl -i -X POST -d "service=http://localhost:8080/yywl/home.do" http://localhost:8082/cas/v1/tickets/TGT-1-14VWRxYUchN5AZhsnXqJ0cS5nYk9cNb7o4BezkKfWD7cbYUBaj-cas01.example.org

// 登录应用系统
http://localhost:8080/yywl/home.do?ticket=ST-3-9QkpLsFmCEqIXSVvGH9P-cas

// 注销
curl -i  -X DELETE http://localhost:8080/cas/v1/tickets/TGT-1-14VWRxYUchN5AZhsnXqJ0cS5nYk9cNb7o4BezkKfWD7cbYUBaj-cas01.example.org
```






```
ST Service Ticket只能使用一次
Service Ticket 有生命周期
１个cookie+Ｎ个session:各应用会创建自己的session表示是否登录
```

aufs : 高级层叠统一文件系统
base image : 基础镜像
btrfs : BTree文件系统
build : 通过docker-file生成docker-images的过程
cgroups : linux内核提供的机制,用于进程组资源限制[CPU,memory,disk I/O,network,etcc]
compose : 定义复杂应用程序[基于多个容器的应用程序]
container : 容器,image镜像的运行实例,包括[镜像,执行环境,执行集][running,paused,stopped]
data volume : 数据卷,用于保存持久化数据,独立于容器生命周期
docker : docker工程,docker守护进程
docker-hub : docker资源服务-镜像服务,用户授权,镜像自动构建,工作流,集成git
docker-file : 构建镜像的指令集
filesystem : 文件系统[ext4,aufs,btrfs,zfs,ntfs,hfs+]
image : 镜像-对应maven中的包
libcontainer : 提供了Go语言实现,创建容器指定[namespace,cgroups,capabilities,fs]
libnetwork :提供Go语言实现,管理容器[network namespace,etc network resources]
link : 历史遗留接口,同一主机上的容器之间相互通信
machine : 简单创建docker主机的工具
overlay network driver : 提供基于网络的同一集群中的容器之间的能力
overlay storage driver : 提供文件系统服务实现对其他文件系统挂载
registry : 镜像资源库注册表
repository :镜像资源库,可以推送到注册表
swarm : 是docker提供的一种集群工具
tag : 镜像标签
toolbox : 为Windows用户,Mac用户提供的安装器
unionFS : provide the building blocks for containers
Union mount : 将多个目录联合成一个目录

! STEPS
!! install docker-toolbox, get docker-machine
* check system version
* easy install
* verfied install result

!! running whalesay image
```
docker run docker/whalesay cowsay boo
docker images
```
!! build image
```
FROM docker/whalesay:latest
RUN apt-get -y update && apt-get install -y fortunes
CMD /usr/games/fortune -a | cowsay
```
```
docker build -t docker-whale
```
!! tag image
```
docker tag 7d9495d03763 limix/docker-whale:latest
```
!! push image
```
docker login --username=limix --email=coollimix@gmail.com
docker push limix/docker-whale:latest
```

! 构建私有仓库
```
docker pull registry:2.1.1
docker run -d -v /opt/registry:/var/lib/registry -p 5000:5000 --restart=always --name registry registry:2.1.1
```

// 创建索引
curl -XPUT http://localhost:9200/index

curl -XPOST http://localhost:9200/index/fulltext/_mapping -d'
{
    "fulltext": {
             "_all": {
            "analyzer": "ik_max_word",
            "search_analyzer": "ik_max_word",
            "term_vector": "no",
            "store": "false"
        },
        "properties": {
            "content": {
                "type": "string",
                "store": "no",
                "term_vector": "with_positions_offsets",
                "analyzer": "ik_max_word",
                "search_analyzer": "ik_max_word",
                "include_in_all": "true",
                "boost": 8
            }
        }
    }
}'

curl -XPOST http://localhost:9200/index/fulltext/1 -d'
{"content":"周扒皮"}
'

// 分词结果测试

!! about
IK_analyzer

!! 中文分词
* 基于词典
* 基于统计
* 基于规则

!! 分词算法
* 最大长度分词 例如中华人民共和国, position=1,offsetstart=0,offsetend=7
* 最大粒度 中华人民共和国 中华人民 中华 华人 人民共和国 共和国 共和 国


!! 问题描述
```
对于文档"科大讯飞" --> 被分词为 "科大" "讯飞"
如果我通过 "大讯" 进行检索, queryString预处理,会分词为 大 讯
进而检索不到需要的文档

对于文档"高中国家" --> 被分词为 "高中" "国家"
如果我通过"中国" 进行检索 queryString 预处理,会被分词为 中国
```

!! CRS {{geo.glossary##CRS}}
* GCS {{geo.glossary##GCS}} 


* PCS {{geo.glossary##PCS}} 
** 投影坐标系由两项参数确定 
** 地理坐标系,由基准面确定, 例如北京54,西安80,WGS84
** 投影方法,高斯-克吕格,lambert投影

* WGS {{geo.glossary##WGS}}

> 基准面是利用特定椭球体对特定地区表面的逼近,因此每个国家或者地区,均有各自的基准面,如WGC1984(GPS点) Xian 1980.prj Beijing 1954.prj






<<tabs "[tag[geo]tag[business]![geo.business]]">>
























> 百度地图的热力图使用的是heatmap.js实现的

!! 客户端解决方案
* heatmap.js 
** 局限性:需要从客户端来进行渲染,客户端渲染的压力比较大.
!! 服务端解决方案
* geoserver.service.wps 生成点图







> projection:{{geo.glossary##projection}}

* Mercator Projection 属于平面直角坐标的一种,和球面坐标相对应
> 又名“等角正轴圆柱投影”，荷兰地图学家墨卡托（Mercator）在1569年拟定，假设地球被围在一个中空的圆柱里，其赤道与圆柱相接触，然后再假想地球中心有一盏灯，把球面上的图形投影到圆柱体上，再把圆柱体展开，这就是一幅标准纬线为零度（即赤道）的“墨卡托投影”绘制出的世界地图。

http://www.cnblogs.com/beniao/archive/2010/04/18/1714544.html

!! 墨卡托投影
* EPSG:900913
* ~~ESRI:102113~~
* ESRI:102100
* ~~EPSG:3785~~ 和ESRI:102113相对应
* EPSG:3587 - was never a real EPSG code --> 未正常使用过
* EPSG:3857 球形墨卡托投影坐标的一种

animate:动画
animation:动画
arcGrid:a coverage file format created by ESRI
bounding box:边界框
bounding boxes:边界框 对应的 min-x,min-y,max-x,max-y
capabilities document:能力描述文档
coordinate:坐标
coverage:覆盖,范围
CRS:(coordinate referrence system 坐标参考系统)
datasource:数据源
Declared SRS:我们想要显示的地图参考坐标系统
dimensions:尺寸
disk quotas:磁盘配额
DPI:(Dots Per Inch 每英寸打印的点)
ESRI:Environmental Systems Research Institute-美国环境系统研究所公司
feature:要素,LIMIX_TODO:有哪些常见的要素?
footway:人行道
geographic:地理
geometry:几何图形
GCS:(geographic coordinate system 地理空间坐标系-又称球面坐标,使用经纬度坐标描述地球上某一点所处的位置,某一个地理坐标系是基于一个基准面定义的)
GeoWebCache:采用Java实现用于缓存WMS-Tile的开源项目
GEOS:Geometry Engine OpenSource 地理引擎
GML:Geography MarkupLanguage 地理标记语言
gridSet:EPSG:4326,EPSG:900913
grid:网格
ground resolution:地面分辨率,一个像素(pixel)代表的地面尺寸(米), 屏幕距离P/(72*39.3701) 
highway:道路

imagery:影像-通过各种遥感设备,传感器,或者照相机得到的电子的或者纸质的图片,最小单元为像素,参考raster栅格最小单元像元.
JTS:Java Topology Suite
KML:Keyhole标记语言,OGC维护的国际标准,可以将Google Maps理解为KML浏览器
Lat/Lon:维度精度包围盒
latitude:维度
longitude:经度
layer:图层
mapadc:中国领先的基础地图服务提供商
matrix:矩阵
Native SRS:地图数据本身的坐标系统
Decleare SRS:声明的坐标系统
OGC:开放地理空间信息联盟
openGis:OGI标准
openlayer:Web GIS 客户端开发提供的javascript库
overlay:覆盖
OSM:OpenStreetMap-开源WIKI地图
OWS: OGC Web service is an OGC Standard
PCS:[projection coordinate system][投影坐标系统]又称平面直角坐标,使用基于x,y值的坐标系统来描述地球上某个点所处的位置.是从地球的近似椭体投影得到的,平面坐标系统的投影通常是以米为单位的
pixel:像素
pre-rendered:预渲染
projection:投影,国内谷歌,高德,腾讯,用标准-墨卡托投影
raster:栅格(一种数据模型),特指影像的存储方式,栅格最小单元,像元.cell,对应影像最小单元像素.
panning the map:移动地图
residential:居住区
rotation:旋转
restaurant:餐厅
resolution:分辨率,地图实际高度或者实际宽度,和div(以像素大小)的比值,其中地图大小为米,每个像元代表的实地距离.
render:渲染,分为服务器渲染,客户端渲染mapnik,客户端渲染有,Canvas,DOM,WebGL
scales:比例尺,地图上距离与实际距离的比例
scale denominator:比例尺分母,例如在SLD中会使用,MaxScaleDenominator,比例尺分母最大值,分辨率resolution
shapefile:ESRI 美国环境系统研究所公司所研制的GIS文件系统格式文件,是工业标准的矢量数据文件.扩展名.shp
SLD:Styled Layer Descriptor风格化图层描述器[要素自定义]-描述了如何在WMS规范基础上进行扩展使之支持用户对要素数据进行自定义的符号化显示,基于XML的OGC标准
spatial:空间
SRS:[spatial reference system] 空间参考系统,例如EPSG:4326,EPSG:900913
store:tell server how to connect a shapefile
symbolization:符号化
vector:矢量
WGS:(World Geodetic System 世界大地坐标系)
WCS:Web Coverage Service 地理覆盖服务-提供的是包含了地理位置信息或属性的空间栅格图层
WFS:Web Feature Service WEB要素服务
WMS-C:Web Map Service cached
WMS:Web Map Service 地图服务
WMTS:Web Map Tile Service WEB地图瓦片服务






!!组成
* A spatial reference system (EPSG code) 空间参考系统
  ** 常见的有 EPSG4326
* A bounding box describing the extent
* One of either a list of scale denominators, resolutions, or zoom levels. 包含的有比例尺,分辨率,缩放级别
* The tile dimensions in pixels (constant for all zoom levels) 像素尺寸,例如像素尺寸为256*256
* (Optional) Pixel size (to calculate scales). The default is 0.28mm/pixel, corresponding to 90.71428571428572 DPI{{geo.glossary##DPI}}






```
屏幕距离: 指的是屏幕上像素点的个数,假定为P
图上距离: P/72/39.3701m-屏幕上点的个数,72个像素点一英寸,再换算成米
分辨率: 地面宽度/count(pix) 简单理解为一个像素点所代表的地面距离
实地距离: P*R = 像素点个数*每个像素点所代表的地面距离
比例尺: 图上距离和实地距离之比
```






A gridsubset is a layer-specific definition specifying








!! 定义
WMTS {{geo.glossary##WMTS}} 将配置好的''一定坐标范围''的地图,按照''固定若干个比例尺''和''指定图片尺寸'',在服务端切割成''若干行及列的正方形图片'',以指定的格式保存成图像文件,''按一定的命名规则和组织方式''存储到服务器的目录系统中或是数据库系统里形成''金字塔模型''的静态地图缓存.

!! 理论基础
金字塔模型

!! 不足
数据同步更新问题,

# 区分几个常见的概念,比例尺.scale,分辨率.resolution,地图范围.extent,缩放级

# 要想离线看到GIS地图必须有底图切片数据
# 地图切片数据和地图瓦片数据有什么关联关系?
> 将地图划分为一个个的网格-现在一般都是一个切片对应一个图片
> 瓦片:每个比例尺上对地图进行切片
# 可以使用底图下载器下载切片数据
# 区分栅格类型和矢量类型的不同数据源 http://blog.csdn.net/redhairp/article/details/7238227
# 已知GosServer集成版没有发布ArcGis切片的功能
# 区分底图和专题图层的不同

! Osmosis or osm2pgsql
osm2pgsql支持数据更新,属于比较通用的方式.







!!方案一
OSM提携架构离线地图方案

# 从官网下载需要的离线数据
# 将离线数据导入到postgresql/postgis数据库当中
# 使用renderd驻守渲染接受请求
# 使用mapnik对矢量地图数据进行实际的渲染
# 通过apache的mod_tile模块提供瓦片服务

!! 优点
* 地图样式开发相对简单

!! 缺点
* 仅仅是瓦片服务器,功能上相对有限

```
service=WMS    // 请求的协议
version=1.1.0  // 请求的版本
request=GetMap // 请求类型
layers=osm-postgis-test:planet_osm_line // 请求的图层
styles= // 指定的图层样式,SLD
bbox=5290329.27,4062797.52,7535498.69,5941692.78 // 
width=768
height=642
srs=EPSG:3857
```

!! NamedLayer,UserLayer有什么区别和联系?
> 答:NamedLayer和UserLayer的区分是根据是否定义图层,NamedLayer是WMS中的图层,UserLayer是用户根据WCS,WFS来定义一个图层,并且添加样式.
> 获得陈述对象,陈述对象从WMS中获取，UserLayer成熟对象图层由用户在样式中定义.

```xml
其中UserLayer可以自己通过OWS定义图层
<xsd:choice minOccurs="0">
<xsd:element ref="sld:RemoteOWS"/>
<xsd:element ref="sld:InlineFeature"/>
</xsd:choice>
```

!! NameStyle,UserStyle有什么区别和联系?
> 答: NamedStyle和UserStyle是根据Style的状态确定的.NamedStyle是WMS发布Style,UserStyle是用户定义的样式.
```
<StyledLayerDescriptor version="1.1.0">
  <name>planet-osm-line</name>
  <NamedLayer>
  	<sld:Name>world</sld:Name>
  </NamedLayer>
</StyledLayerDescriptor>
```
```
<StyledLayerDescriptor version="1.1.0">
  <name>planet-osm-line</name>
  <UserLayer></UserLayer>
</StyledLayerDescriptor>

```

* 地图中的桥的样式设计有点问题,需要修复.. 
* 需要下载地图作为底图
** 通过地图下载器下载需要的底图
*** 空擎地图助手
*** 全能电子地图下载器 非免费,需要购买服务,功能比较强大
*** 水经注
*** 太乐地图下载器,支持地图格式选择,发布成wmts服务,兴趣点,坐标纠偏
*** 稻歌软件工作室,新版本有问题
** 根据OSM生成所需要的底图

* 需要支持实现POI数据的检索

* 如何支持定制的业务数据图层-> 考虑需要动态数据库技术支持,不能局限于静态数据

* 跨域解析支持 -> 默认提供此开关选项

* 需要GeoServer中集成GeoWebCache还是采用独立的GeoWebCache提供服务?
> 集成版本自动将图层以瓦片形式发布

* 虽然GeoWebCache能发布预先生成的松散型瓦片,但并不能抽取和截断这些图层,GeoWebCache只支持融合性的缓存瓦片

* 客户端开发,可以采取openlayers.总体感觉不是特别复杂的应用
* 迁移到OSM

!! 关于
包括两种类型,矢量数据源-vector,栅格数据源-raster. 例如OSM开放的矢量数据源,数据格式有shapefile和postgis两种格式.

!! vector datasource 矢量数据源
* shapefiles
* shapefile
* PostGis数据库
* PostGid(JNDI) 数据
* properties
* WFS Web Feature Service

!! raster datasource 栅格数据源
* ArcGid arc grid coverage format

```javascript
// 定义匿名函数
(function($){
	$.ajaxSetup({   
        contentType:"application/x-www-form-urlencoded;charset=utf-8",   
        error:function(XMLHttpRequest,textStatus){ 
        // 通过XMLHttpRequest取得响应头 sessionstatus，  
        var sessionstatus=XMLHttpRequest.getResponseHeader("sessionstatus"); 
        if(sessionstatus=="timeout"){ 
          window.location.replace(ctx + "/login");   
        }   
      } 
	});
})(jquery);

```
PID:进程ID
USER:进程所有者
PR:进程优先级
NI:nice负值表示高优先级,正值表示低优先级
VIRT:表示进程虚拟内存总量,单位KB，VIRT=SWAP+RES
SHR:表示共享内存大小,单位KB
S:表示进程状态,D:不可终端睡眠,R:运行,S睡眠,T跟踪,停止,Z僵尸进程
%CPU:上次更新到现在的CPU时间占用百分比
%MEM:进程使用的物理内存百分比
TIME+:进程使用的CPU时间总计，单位1/100秒
COMMAND:进程名称
```

!! 安装步骤

// python head file not found

sudo yum install sqlite
sudo yum install turbojpeg
sudo yum install turbojpeg-devel
sudo yum install libtiff
sudo yum install libtiff-devel
sudo yum install freetype
sudo yum install freetype-devel
sudo yum install libxml2
sudo yum install libxml2-devel
--> TODO libproj
sudo yum install cairo
sudo yum install cairo-devel
sudo yum install pycairo
sudo yum install pycairo-devel



cd ~/src

cd mapnik
git submodule update --init

python scons/scons.py configure INPUT_PLUGINS=all OPTIMIZATION=3 SYSTEM_FONTS=/usr/share/fonts/truetype/


JOBS=1 make
sudo make install
sudo ldconfig
```

!! 修改方法
```
// 关闭密码强制校验
plugin-load=validate_password.so
validate-password=OFF
// 关闭大小写敏感
lower_case_table_names=1
修改数据库默认编码
character_set_server=utf8 // LIMIX_INFO 修改默认编码格式
show variables like 'character%'

select @@sql_mode;
需要在服务端执行操作

SET sql_mode=`STRICT_TRANS_TABLES,NO_ZERO_IN_DATE,NO_ZERO_DATE,ERROR_FOR_DIVISION_BY_ZERO,NO_AUTO_CREATE_USER,NO_ENGINE_SUBSTITUTION`;

'ONLY_FULL_GROUP_BY,STRICT_TRANS_TABLES,NO_ZERO_IN_DATE,NO_ZERO_DATE,ERROR_FOR_DIVISION_BY_ZERO,NO_AUTO_CREATE_USER,NO_ENGINE_SUBSTITUTION'

set global sql_mode=`STRICT_TRANS_TABLES,NO_ZERO_IN_DATE,NO_ZERO_DATE,ERROR_FOR_DIVISION_BY_ZERO,NO_AUTO_CREATE_USER,NO_ENGINE_SUBSTITUTION`
```

!! 函数date_format
```
DATE_FORMA T(date, format) 
```


!! 常见格式
```
%Y-%m-%d %H:%i%S.%f
```

!! 参考
```
格式 	描述
%a	缩写星期名
%b	缩写月名
%c	月，数值
%D	带有英文前缀的月中的天
%d	月的天，数值(00-31)
%e	月的天，数值(0-31)
%f	微秒
%H	小时 (00-23)
%h	小时 (01-12)
%I	小时 (01-12)
%i	分钟，数值(00-59)
%j	年的天 (001-366)
%k	小时 (0-23)
%l	小时 (1-12)
%M	月名
%m	月，数值(00-12)
%p	AM 或 PM
%r	时间，12-小时（hh:mm:ss AM 或 PM）
%S	秒(00-59)
%s	秒(00-59)
%T	时间, 24-小时 (hh:mm:ss)
%U	周 (00-53) 星期日是一周的第一天
%u	周 (00-53) 星期一是一周的第一天
%V	周 (01-53) 星期日是一周的第一天，与 %X 使用
%v	周 (01-53) 星期一是一周的第一天，与 %x 使用
%W	星期名
%w	周的天 （0=星期日, 6=星期六）
%X	年，其中的星期日是周的第一天，4 位，与 %V 使用
%x	年，其中的星期一是周的第一天，4 位，与 %v 使用
%Y	年，4 位
%y	年，2 位
```

```
ERROR 1045 (28000): Access denied for user 'root'@'localhost' (using password: YES)
1. 进入安全模式,重置密码
mysqld_safe --init-file=/home/me/mysql-init &
>5.7.6 ALTER USER 'root'@'localhost' IDENTIFIED BY 'MyNewPass';
<5.7.6 SET PASSWORD FOR 'root'@'localhost' = PASSWORD('12');
2. 重启服务,进入正常模式
update mysql.user set authentication_string = PASSWORD('MyNewPass'), password_expired = 'N'
    where User = 'root' AND Host = 'localhost';
FLUSH PRIVILEGES;
```

map:layers,a view,interactions to modify map content,controls with UI components.
layers:图层
view:视窗
interactions:交互

参考:http://openlayers.org/en/latest/doc/tutorials/concepts.html






!! 特征
* Objectives
* Closure Tools
* Public API
* Custom Builds
* Renderers and Browser Support
* Objects and Naming Conventions 命名规范
** top-level ol namespace
** further namespaces, such as ol.layer; lower-case initial
** types which have an upper-case initial. 类大写
** the subclasses repeat the superclass type in their name
*** 例如 ol/layer/vectorlayer.js
** the names of private properties and methods, that is, those that are not part of the API, end in an underscore. 私有成员下划线强调












> 图层是对数据进行了可视化 A layer is a visual representation of data from a source.

!! 瓦片图层 ol.layer.Tile 
> 预渲染网格瓦片图层 pre-rendered,  tiled images in grids
!! 服务器渲染图层 ol.layer.Image
> server rendered images that are available for arbitrary extents and resolutions
!! 客户端渲染矢量图层 ol.layer.Vector
> 客户端渲染 is for vector data that is rendered client-side 可由客户端提供SLD进行渲染
!! 客户端渲染矢量瓦片图层 ol.layer.VectorTile







!! 定义
> A map is made of layers, a view to visualize them, interactions to modify map content and controls with UI components. 由图层,视图,交互,控制组成

```
<div id="map" style="width: 100%, height: 400px"></div>
<script>
  var map = new ol.Map({target: 'map'});
</script>
```







```
1. 在地图上叠加矢量图层,需要WFS
2. 请求方式分为 KVP,REST
```

!! 安装后处理
```
// 中国台湾处理
select * from planet_osm_point where way = '0101000020110F00003D0AD71301B06941B81E854B8CFB4441';

// 更新为台湾
update planet_osm_point set place = 'state',name='台湾' where way='0101000020110F00003D0AD71301B06941B81E854B8CFB4441';

!! 创建OSM数据库-集群
```
pg_dropcluster --stop 9.3 main
pg_createcluster [options] version name 
例如 
pg_createcluster -u postgres -d /iflytek/data/pgsql/9.3/osm -e utf-8 --start 9.3 osm
Creating new cluster 9.3/osm ...
  config /etc/postgresql/9.3/osm
  data   /iflytek/data/pgsql/9.3/osm
  locale zh_HK.UTF-8
  port   5432
pg_lsclusters
Ver Cluster Port Status Owner    Data directory              Log file
9.3 osm     5432 online postgres /iflytek/data/pgsql/9.3/osm /var/log/postgresql/postgresql-9.3-osm.log
```

!!! 调整postgres参数 /etc/postgresql/9.3/osm/postgresql.conf
```
shared_buffers = 20480MB 
checkpoint_segments = 50
checkpoint_completion_target=0.9
maintenance_work_mem = 2048M 
autovacuum = off
max_connections = 1000
listen_addresses = '*'
effective_cache_size = 16GB
bgwriter_lru_maxpages= 500
#synchronous_commit=on // 异步提交



shared_buffers: 数据库服务器将使用的共享内存缓冲区大小，该缓冲区为所有连接共用。从磁盘读入的数据（主要包括表和索引）都缓存在这里.// 例如生产现场的缓存是125G, 我分配了20G,创建索引的时候发现速度比较慢,因而后面该考虑增大该配置到40G,用于快速处理索引表信息.
checkpoint_segments: 定量，写入大小。一个是16MB，默认是3，所以就是48MB。到了这个量就会调用写入处理 16M*20=320MB
maintenance_work_mem: 定义的内存只是在CREATE INDEX, VACUUM等时用到，因此用到的频率不高，但是往往这些指令消耗比较多的资源，因此应该尽快让这些指令快速执行完毕-> 考虑到后面有创建索引等操作,需要将该值设置为20G

autovacuum: 必须设置,否则等着磁盘崩溃
```
!!! 调整参数改为MD5
```
/etc/postgresql/9.3/osm/pg_hba.conf
local   all postgres   peer
local   all all        md5                           
```

!! 数据库环境
```
// 创建数据库
sudo -u postgres -i
createuser gis # answer yes for superuser (although this isn't strictly necessary)
createdb -E UTF8 -O gis gis
exit

// 操作系统中添加用户
sudo useradd -m gis
sudo passwd gis

// 为数据库用户添加post-gis插件扩展支持
sudo -u postgres psql
\c gis
CREATE EXTENSION postgis;
create extension hstore;
ALTER TABLE geometry_columns OWNER TO gis;
ALTER TABLE spatial_ref_sys OWNER TO gis;
\q
exit
```
!! 启动数据库
```
// 检查配置参数是否完整
1. 检查数据库基础配置
grep -x "[^#]\w.*" /etc/postgresql/9.3/osm/postgresql.conf
2. 高可靠性配置 host-based authentication file
grep -x "[^#]\w.*" /etc/postgresql/9.3/osm/pg_hba.conf
3. 标示 ident configuration file
/etc/postgresql/9.3/osm/pg_ident.conf

cat /etc/postgresql/9.3/osm/postgresql.conf | grep 'checkpoint_segments\|maintenance_work_mem\|shared_buffers\|autovacuum'

pg_ctlclusters 来启动需要的数据库实例
pg_ctlcluster 9.3 osm restart

/usr/lib/postgresql/9.3/bin/postgres -D /iflytek/data/pgsql/9.3/osm -c config_file=/etc/postgresql/9.3/osm/postgresql.conf



show max_connections;
service postgresql status
service postgresql stop
service postgresql start
```


!! 添加导入程序
```
git clone git://github.com/openstreetmap/osm2pgsql.git
cd osm2pgsql
mkdir build
cd build
cmake -DCMAKE_PREFIX_PATH=/usr/local/pgsql .. -LH
make
sudo make install
```

!! 导入数据到gis数据库
```
lscpu
// 注意:切换到用户 postgres 后执行 su postgres
sudo -u postgres nohup osm2pgsql -U postgres -d gis-C 60000  --number-processes 100 --hstore -s -S ./default.style /iflytek/data/osm/src/planet-160530.osm.pbf > log.file 2>&1 &

注意使用不要使用选项 -s 否则会将中间结果也放入到数据库当中,导入速度慢.正常模式,导入结束后丢弃,速度较快.
```

!! 将world_boundaries.tar.gz解压到目录 
```
tar zxvf world_boundaries.tar.gz -C /usr/local/share/


psql -d gis  
alter user postgres with password 'iflytek'; 
```

!! 更改参数
```
pg_ctlcluster 9.3 osm stop
调整参数
maintenance_work_mem = 40960MB
shared_buffers = 40960MB

// 清理缓存
echo 1 > /proc/sys/vm/drop_caches
pg_ctlcluster 9.3 osm start

// 检查启动日志
tail -f /var/log/postgresql/postgresql-9.3-osm.log
2016-07-07 03:39:21 MSK LOG:  MultiXact member wraparound protections are now enabled
2016-07-07 03:39:21 MSK LOG:  database system is ready to accept connections
```

!! 执行脚本
```
sudo -u postgres -i
cp /iflytek/data/geoserver/gis.sql ~/
psql gis
\i gis.sql
```

```
执行完成后
psql:gis.sql:964: NOTICE: table "theme_park"
```

!! 部署应用
```
1. 将geoserver-data.tar.gz 解压到 /iflytek/data 目录下面
2. 将geo.tar.gz 加压到 /iflytek/server/ 目录下面 ==> 统一修改JAVA_HOME
3. 修改 /iflytek/server/geo/webapps/ROOT/test/index.html 
   修改IP为准确的IP地址
4. 更改连接的源头GIS的连接数量为 100个连接
5. 修改gis的密码为iflytek-检查store是否有效,失效状态下,勾选,并且根据需要调大数值
6. 创建安全目录 
   /iflytek/data/gwc/iflytek 
   /iflytek/data/gwc/ispp
   /iflytek/data/gwc/default
7. 为图层组配置缓存目录,后面统一配置好了
8. 解决问题:设置缓存无效问题(后面需要解决背景色更改了,请求,不缓存的问题)
9. EPSG:900913 和EPSG3857是否可以等同
```







!!! 检查内核参数
```
1. 方式1: sudo sysctl kernel.shmmax
   kernel.shmmax = 18446744073692774399
2. 方式2：cat /proc/sys/kernel/shmmax
   18446744073692774399
```

!!! 修改内核参数方法[如果内核相关参数过小,可调整]
```
1. 添加内核配置参数: 配置文件: /etc/sysctl.conf
# Increase kernel shared memory segments 
# needed for large databases
kernel.shmmax=268435456
2. 检查更新后的内核配置参数
sudo sysctl kernel.shmmax
```

```
1. crs和srs具有什么区别联系?
   CRS Coordinate Reference System 坐标参考系统
   SRS Spatial Reference System 空间坐标参考系统
   在wms地图服务中,wms1.1请求参数是srs,而在wms接口中使用crs参数

2. 更改地图名称
   // 登录到用户
   sudo -u postgres -i
   // 连接数据库
   psql gis
   // 查询图层中对应数据的名称记录
   select * from placenames_large where name like '台%';
   // 更新
   update placenames_large set name = '台湾' where id = 具体的id

// 九寨沟
http://192.168.76.30:20080/geoserver/gwc/service/wms?SERVICE=WMS&VERSION=1.3.0&REQUEST=GetMap&FORMAT=image%2Fpng&TRANSPARENT=false&LAYERS=iflytek%3Aosm1&tiled=true&SRS=EPSG%3A3857&WIDTH=256&HEIGHT=256&CRS=EPSG%3A3857&STYLES=&BBOX=11584184.510675032%2C3874440.0897190142%2C11593968.450295534%2C3884224.029339517

```
git clone git://github.com/openstreetmap/osm2pgsql.git
cd osm2pgsql
mkdir build
cd build
cmake -DCMAKE_PREFIX_PATH=/usr/local/pgsql .. -LH
make
sudo make install
```

Database options:

                        environment variable or use -W).

osm2pgsql -a -U postgres -d gis --host 192.168.84.151 --password --hstore -s -S ./default.style ~/data/repo/china-latest.osm.pbf

!! 模式转换
```
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS admin_01234;
DELETE FROM geometry_columns WHERE f_table_name = 'admin_01234';
CREATE TABLE admin_01234 AS SELECT way,admin_level
       from planet_osm_roads
       where "boundary"='administrative'
         and admin_level in ('0','1','2','3','4');
ALTER TABLE admin_01234 ADD COLUMN id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY;
INSERT INTO geometry_columns VALUES ( '', 'public', 'admin_01234', 'way', 2, 3857, 'GEOMETRY');
CREATE INDEX admin_01234_idx ON admin_01234 USING GIST(way);
commit;
```

!! 定义
```
   Column    |           Type            |                        Modifiers                         
-------------+---------------------------+----------------------------------------------------------
 way         | geometry(LineString,3857) | 
 admin_level | text                      | 
 id          | integer                   | not null default nextval('admin_01234_id_seq'::regclass)

"admin_01234_pkey" PRIMARY KEY, btree (id)
"admin_01234_idx" gist (way)
```

!! OSM数据结构
* 空间数据
** Node 通过经纬度定义一个地理坐标点,同时可以使用height=*标识物体海拔,通过layer=*和level=* 可以标示物体所在的地图层面与所在建筑物的层数
** Way 通过2-2000个nodes构成了way，way可以表示三种图形事物,非闭合线,闭合线,区域.
** Relation 用来描述两个或多个基元的相互关系(nodes,ways或者其他relations) 相互的关系通过role来定义.
*** route 定义公路
*** 多个多边形 定义area例如建筑,河堤
*** 边界 装门用来定义行政边界
*** 限制 用来描述限制比如非左转
* 属性数据
** Tag 标签不是地图基本元素,但是各元素通过tag来记录数据信息.通过key/value来对数据进行记录,例如highway=residential来定义居住区道路.同时支持命名空间,maxspeed:winter=*表示冬天最高限速

!!OSM数据格式
# OSM XML xml-format provided by the API
# PBF highly compressed,optimized binary format similar to the API
# o5m for high-speed processing,uses PBF coding
# OSMJSON json variant of OSM XML

> The two main formats used are PBF or compressed OSM XML.






amenity:礼仪
boundary:边界
landuse:土地利用

Bing highres:
town:
local:

religious_administration:

```
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS housenames;
DELETE FROM geometry_columns WHERE f_table_name = 'housenames';
CREATE TABLE housenames AS SELECT way,"addr:housename" from planet_osm_polygon where "addr:housename" is not null and building is not null
       union
       select way,"addr:housename" from planet_osm_point where "addr:housename" is not null;
ALTER TABLE housenames ADD COLUMN id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY;
INSERT INTO geometry_columns VALUES ( '', 'public', 'housenames', 'way', 2, 3857, 'GEOMETRY');
CREATE INDEX housenames_idx ON housenames USING GIST(way);

!! 说明
!! 模式转换
```
DELETE FROM geometry_columns WHERE f_table_name = 'landcover';
CREATE TABLE landcover AS SELECT way,aeroway,amenity,landuse,leisure,man_made,military,"natural",power,tourism,name,highway,
       case when religion in ('christian','jewish') then religion else 'INT-generic'::text end as religion
       from planet_osm_polygon
       where landuse is not null
          or leisure is not null
          or aeroway in ('apron','aerodrome')
          or amenity in ('parking','university','college','school','hospital','kindergarten','grave_yard','prison')
          or military in ('barracks','danger_area')
          or "natural" in ('field','beach','desert','heath','mud','grassland','wood','sand','scrub')
          or power in ('station','sub_station','generator')
          or tourism in ('attraction','camp_site','caravan_site','picnic_site','zoo')
          or highway in ('services','rest_area')
       order by z_order,way_area desc;
ALTER TABLE landcover ADD COLUMN id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY;
INSERT INTO geometry_columns VALUES ( '', 'public', 'landcover', 'way', 2, 3857, 'GEOMETRY');
CREATE INDEX landcover_idx ON landcover USING GIST(way);
```

```
contains all non-closed ways
additional rows are created for ways which are members of type=route relations

首先需要弄明白几个概念
1. non-closed ways
2. type=route relations
3. type=route relations are concatenated into chunks
```

!! 定义






!! 模式转换
```
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS roads;
DELETE FROM geometry_columns WHERE f_table_name = 'roads';
CREATE TABLE roads AS SELECT way,highway,
       case when tunnel in ('yes','true','1') then 'yes'::text else tunnel end as tunnel,
       case when railway='preserved' and service in ('spur','siding','yard') then 'INT-preserved-ssy'::text else railway end as railway
       from planet_osm_roads
       where highway is not null
          or (railway is not null and railway!='preserved' and (service is null or service not in ('spur','siding','yard')))
          or railway='preserved'
       order by z_order;
ALTER TABLE roads ADD COLUMN id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY;
INSERT INTO geometry_columns VALUES ( '', 'public', 'roads', 'way', 2, 3857, 'GEOMETRY');
CREATE INDEX roads_idx ON roads USING GIST(way);
```






!! 说明
http://wiki.openstreetmap.org/wiki/Key:ref
Common for roads, highway exits, routes, etc


!! 模式转换
```
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS roads_text_ref_low_zoom;
DELETE FROM geometry_columns WHERE f_table_name = 'roads_text_ref_low_zoom';
CREATE TABLE roads_text_ref_low_zoom AS SELECT way,highway,ref,char_length(ref) as length
       from planet_osm_roads
       where highway in ('motorway','trunk','primary','secondary')
         and ref is not null
         and char_length(ref) between 1 and 8;
ALTER TABLE roads_text_ref_low_zoom ADD COLUMN id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY;
INSERT INTO geometry_columns VALUES ( '', 'public', 'roads_text_ref_low_zoom', 'way', 2, 3857, 'GEOMETRY');
CREATE INDEX roads_text_ref_low_zoom_idx ON roads_text_ref_low_zoom USING GIST(way);

!! 坐标系

[[坐标系|geo.crs]]






!! 说明

!! 模式转换
```
DROP TABLE IF EXISTS text;
DELETE FROM geometry_columns WHERE f_table_name = 'text';
CREATE TABLE text AS SELECT way,amenity,shop,access,leisure,landuse,man_made,"natural",place,tourism,ele,name,ref,military,aeroway,waterway,historic,'yes'::text as point
       from planet_osm_point
       where amenity is not null
          or shop in ('supermarket','bakery','clothes','fashion','convenience','doityourself','hairdresser','department_store','butcher','car','car_repair','bicycle','florist')
          or leisure is not null
          or landuse is not null
          or tourism is not null
          or "natural" is not null
          or man_made in ('lighthouse','windmill')
          or place='island'
          or military='danger_area'
          or aeroway='gate'
          or waterway='lock'
          or historic in ('memorial','archaeological_site');
ALTER TABLE text ADD COLUMN id SERIAL PRIMARY KEY;
INSERT INTO geometry_columns VALUES ( '', 'public', 'text', 'way', 2, 3857, 'GEOMETRY');
CREATE INDEX text_idx ON text USING GIST(way);
commit;
```

!! 定义
```

    "text_idx" gist (way)

```
道路标记
highway=motorway fast, restricted access road 高速公路
highway=trunk most important in standard road network
highway=primary …down to…
highway=secondary …
highway=tertiary …
highway=unclassified least important in standard road network
highway=residential smaller road for access mostly to residential properties 住户拥有
highway=service smaller road for access, often but not exclusively to non-residential properties 小道,只提供道路

!历史发展

PAAS将原有的基础资源关注点上升到应用层面,目标是提供一个可简单操作的平台帮助开发人员运行,管理web应用.

约束型PaaS平台:优点,高效利用底层资源,存储,网络资源;缺点:不得不遵守一套独立的规范和API,有可能基础开发语言都会受到平台的约束.例如GAE google apple engine.

开放型Paas平台:其中HeroKu 可以认为是代表

! 解决的具体问题
* PaaS提供一个应用的聚合
  ** 应用服务中间件
  ** 数据存储服务
  ** 消息服务
* PaaS提供服务发现,可伸缩性,状态管理
  ** 服务发现 例如DNS
  ** 可伸缩性
  ** 状态管理
* PaaS中的服务监控、恢复与容灾
* PaaS的Portal门户
* ITIL服务管理的相关内容
* 安全管控
  ** 组成组件的安全
  ** 提供服务的安全控制
* 部署发布相关内容

!! 分布式计算的挑战
* 可扩展性
* 可伸缩性
* 容错性
* 安全性
* 并发性

!! PAAS代表
* 谷歌GAE
* AEB AWS Elastic Beanstalk
* Cloud Foundry
* Heroku













devops:
iaas:基础设施即服务
paas:平台即服务
saas:软件即服务






PAAS将原有的基础资源关注点上升到应用层面,目标是提供一个可简单操作的平台帮助开发人员运行,管理web应用.

约束型PaaS平台:优点,高效利用底层资源,存储,网络资源;缺点:不得不遵守一套独立的规范和API,有可能基础开发语言都会受到平台的约束.例如GAE google apple engine.

开放型Paas平台:其中HeroKu 可以认为是代表






开发人员和运维人员之间的矛盾

前期解决方案[标准化,自动化,自助化]处理


当前我们团队存在的问题-运维工具新语言的负责,运维团队负责-只是实现了自动化,并没有实现标准化,如果开发人员负责,脚本执行发生问题,最终还是转到运维人员..

理论基础

分布式计算






```
1. 缺少持续优化改进机制
   * 识别当前需要最先解决的主要矛盾
   * 针对主要矛盾制定解决办法,以及问题解决检验办法
   * 执行解决办法
   * 检验方法执行效果—并识别下一级矛盾,持续改进现状
   
   * 识别出可执行性的手段,并执行,检查执行结果
2. 当前的现状[现状分析-分析方法]
   * 版本过多-缺少良好的版本更新机制
   * 代码质量层次不齐
   * 业务知识缺失
   * 接口文档缺失
   * 代码不够规范
   * 单元测试不够
   * 属性提取
   * 人员职责划分说明不清楚
   * 例如:js代码数据定义和数据执行混杂在一起,可读性较差,js中过度使用全局空间变量,没有作用域管理理念
2. 缺失业务概念库的管理
3. 缺少程序设计属性概念库
2. 作用域范围划分-例如前端的作用域概念缺少
4. 软件版本控制
   * 软件SVN版本控制
   * maven内部版本控制
   * 各个组件版本控制
5. 无代码退出机制
6. 规范化要求确失
   * 接口设计的过于随意性
7. 没有公用代码提炼过程

8. 代码层面
   * 数据定义详细说明
     * 数据库定义详细文档
     * 作用域对象的详细定义-个人感觉这些信息应该和代码绑定在一起
   * 代码共享机制缺失
   * 代码退出机制缺失,共享代码提取缺失
   * 接口设计规范
```

!! 创建数据库实例
```
sudo -u postgres -i
createuser limix # answer yes for superuser (although this isn't strictly necessary)
createdb -E UTF8 -O limix gis
exit

sudo useradd -m username
sudo passwd username
alter user postgres with PASSWORD 'iflytek';

// 其中limix是访问数据库的用户名,gis是数据库的schema
```

!! 扩展数据库实例
```
sudo -u postgres psql
\c gis
CREATE EXTENSION postgis;
ALTER TABLE geometry_columns OWNER TO username;
ALTER TABLE spatial_ref_sys OWNER TO username;
\q
exit

其中\c gis 表示连接数据库实例gis
```

!! 源代码安装
!!! 下载源文件
> http://www.postgresql.org/ftp/source/v9.4.8
!!! 准备工作
> echo /usr/local/lib >> /etc/ld.so.conf.d/local.conf
!!! 依赖检查以及编译
```
rpm -q readline
rpm -q readline-devel
rpm -q make > 3.80
rpm -q tar
rpm -q zlib
./configure
make
make install
// 编译安装扩展
cd contro
sudo make all
// PostgreSQL, contrib, and documentation successfully made. 
// Ready to install
sudo make install
```
!!! 配置环境变量
```
LD_LIBRARY_PATH=/usr/local/pgsql/lib
export LD_LIBRARY_PATH
配置 /etc/ld.so.conf.d
/sbin/ldconfig /usr/local/pgsql/lib
PATH=/usr/local/pgsql/bin:$PATH
export PATH
MANPATH=/usr/local/pgsql/share/man:$MANPATH
export MANPATH
```

!!! 添加系统管理服务 LIMIX_TODO 到底是怎样来操作的
```
cp contrib/start-scripts/linux /etc/init.d/postgresql
chmod +x /etc/init.d/postgresql
service postgresql status
chkconfig --add postgresql
```

!!! 配置
```
1. 添加数据库用户
adduser postgres
2. 配置数据文件并初始化实例
mkdir /usr/local/pgsql/data
chown postgres /usr/local/pgsql/data
su postgres
/usr/local/pgsql/bin/initdb -D /usr/local/pgsql/data
3. 配置网络权限
/usr/local/pgsql/data/pg_hba.conf 
允许以下网段登陆
host all all 192.168.1.0/24 md5
host all all 192.168.2.0/24 md5
4. 配置链接库
/etc/ld.so.conf 中添加 /usr/local/pgsql/lib/
ldconfig
5. 配置监听
postgresql.conf
listen_addresses = '*'
```
!!! 创建数据库
[[geo.postgresql.createdb]]

!!! 运营管理
```
/usr/local/pgsql/bin/postgres -D /usr/local/pgsql/data >logfile 2>&1 &
或者 /usr/local/pgsql/bin/pg_ctl -D /usr/local/pgsql/data -l logfile start
创建数据库schema实例 /usr/local/pgsql/bin/createdb gis
/usr/local/pgsql/bin/psql gis
```

!! 基本信息
```
\c:连接数据库
\l:列举数据库-相当于mysql中show databases
\d:列举视图和表
\dt:列举表-相当于mysql中show tables
\d tblname: 查看表结构
\di:列举索引
\encoding [字元编码名称]:显示或设定用户端字元编码
\h [名称]:SQL 命令语法上的说明，用 * 显示全部命令
\prompt [文本] 名称:提示用户设定内部变数
\password [USERNAME]:securely change the password for a user
\q:退出 psql 
```
!! 数据库DML
```
create database gis:创建数据库
drop database gis:删除数据库
alter table [表名A] rename to [表名B]
drop table [表名];
alter table [表名] add column [字段名] [类型];
alter table [表名] rename column [字段名A] to [字段名B]; 
alter table [表名] alter column [字段名] drop default; 
insert into 表名 ([字段名m],[字段名n],......) values ([列m的值],[列n的值],......); 
修改表中的某行某列的数据： 
update [表名] set [目标字段名]=[目标值] where [该行特征]; 
删除表中某行数据： 
delete from [表名] where [该行特征]; 
delete from [表名];--删空整个表 
```






Grand Unified Configuration Settings

!!8中基本类型

```
boolean: on|off true|false 例如 enable_seqscan
integer: 700  例如 max_connections=700
float: random_page_cost = 3.75
Memory / Disk Size: work_mem = 512MB shared_buffers = 4096
time: authentication_timeout = 30s
string: log_directory = 'pg_log'
enum: log_destination = 'csvlog'
list: search_path = 'main, archive, “$user”'
```

!! 6中配置上下文
```
user: 会话级别配置 can be set on per-session basis at runtime

superuser: 可运行时配置,但仅限于超级管理员使用

sighup: 需要重启 requires a soft restart of the postmaster to change

postmaster: can only be changed with a hard restart

backend: developer settings which have to be set before session start

internal: compile-time settings provided for reference
```

!! 存放位置

!! About
AOF:AppendOnly File的简写,是redis系统提供了一种记录redis操作的持久化方案,在AOF生成的文件中,将忠实记录在redis中发生的操作

!! 操作过程
```
1. 设置配置文件
appendonly yes
appendfsync no // 代表 依赖于操作系统的fsync将aof日志同步到磁盘
appendfsync everysec // 默认一秒进行一次fsync同步操作
appendfsync always // 每次执行都会写磁盘,性能有影响

2. 启动redis服务器
redis-server /etc/redis/6379.conf &
redis-client save
/var/lib/redis/6379/

3. 检查保存后的结果信息
127.0.0.1:6379> keys *
1) "engl-NS_S"
2) "uyhu-NS_S"
3) "uyhu-NPP"
4) "intention-categories"
127.0.0.1:6379> 
```








```
/etc/redis/6379.conf
/var/lib/redis/6379/
```






```
DENIED Redis is running in protected mode because protected mode is enabled, no bind address was specified, no authentication password is requested to clients. In this mode connections are only accepted from the loopback interface. If you want to connect from external computers to Redis you may adopt one of the following solutions: 1) Just disable protected mode sending the command 'CONFIG SET protected-mode no' from the loopback interface by connecting to Redis from the same host the server is running, however MAKE SURE Redis is not publicly accessible from internet if you do so. Use CONFIG REWRITE to make this change permanent. 2) Alternatively you can just disable the protected mode by editing the Redis configuration file, and setting the protected mode option to 'no', and then restarting the server. 3) If you started the server manually just for testing, restart it with the '--protected-mode no' option. 4) Setup a bind address or an authentication password. NOTE: You only need to do one of the above things in order for the server to start accepting connections from the outside.
```

SLD实例:http://docs.geoserver.org/stable/en/user/styling/sld-cookbook/

symbology:符号
SE:Symbology Encoding,符号编码标准
opacity:不透明度
denominator:比例尺


FeatureTypeStyle:要素样式,包含一个或者多个Rule元素
Rule:规则
Filter:过滤器
PropertyIsLessThan:小于某个值的过滤器
PropertyIsGreaterThan:大于某个值的过滤器
PropertyName:属性字段名
Literal:属性值

Symbolizer:符号
PointSymbolizer:点符号
LineSymbolizer:线符号
PloygonSymbolizer:面符号
TextSymbolizer:文字符号
RasterSymbolizer:影像符号

# 组成元素
Graphic:图形


#动作
GraphicFill:图形填充

CssParameter name="fill":填充颜色
CssParameter name="font-family":字体
CssParameter name="font-style":字体样式
CssParameter name="font-size":字体大小






access:是否允许访问
admin-01234:管理
capital:首都-可以认为是level 5单位

basin:盆地
continents:大洲
metropolitan:都市
highway junctions:高速公路路口
tunnels fill:隧道填充
turning circle casing:回转壳体
legend:图例

water:水
marsh:沼泽
wetland:湿地
glaciers:冰川
marinas:码头
reservoir:水库






> NamedLayer specifies an existing layer to be styled, and the styling to apply to it. The styling may be any combination of catalog styles and explicitly-defined styles. If no style is specified, the default style for the layer is used.

> 命名图层为一个已经存在的图层定义样式,样式可能是目录样式,或者明确定义的样式.如果没有定义样式,使用默认样式.

> NamedLayer,UserLayer区别,对服务器而言,前者可以被感知,有命名,后者对服务器不可知,需要明确的要将样式赋予某个图层.














样式:builtup

```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><sld:StyledLayerDescriptor xmlns="http://www.opengis.net/sld" xmlns:sld="http://www.opengis.net/sld" xmlns:ogc="http://www.opengis.net/ogc" xmlns:gml="http://www.opengis.net/gml" version="1.0.0">
  <sld:NamedLayer>
    <sld:Name>builtup</sld:Name>
    <sld:UserStyle>
      <sld:Name>builtup</sld:Name>
      <sld:FeatureTypeStyle>
        <sld:Name>name</sld:Name>
        <sld:Rule>
          <sld:MinScaleDenominator>400000.0</sld:MinScaleDenominator>
          <sld:MaxScaleDenominator>3000000.0</sld:MaxScaleDenominator>
          <sld:PolygonSymbolizer>
            <sld:Fill>
              <sld:CssParameter name="fill">#A6C2DE</sld:CssParameter>
            </sld:Fill>
          </sld:PolygonSymbolizer>
        </sld:Rule>
      </sld:FeatureTypeStyle>
    </sld:UserStyle>
  </sld:NamedLayer>
</sld:StyledLayerDescriptor>
```







```
style:world.sld










```xml
<Rule>
  <Filter></Filter>
  <MinScaleDenominator>12500</MinScaleDenominator>   
  <MaxScaleDenominator>25000</MaxScaleDenominator>
  <LineSymbolizer></LineSymbolizer>
</Rule>
```






```
规律: 比例尺分母越大,线宽越小,比例尺分母月小,线宽月大
该样的比例尺分母很大,属于世界地图全局的范畴
该样式是namedlayer是针对特定图层的样式
相同比例尺,级别越大,线宽越小
```


```
admin_level 2级或3级
比例尺:650,0000 到 5000,0000
stroke-width:0.6,stroke-opacity:0.2,stroke:#800080
```

```
admin_level 4级
比例尺:650,0000 到 5000,0000
stroke-width:0.6,stroke-opacity:0.2,stroke:#800080,dasharray:4 3
```

```
admin_level 2级或3级
比例尺:75,0000 到 6500000
stroke-width:2,stroke-opacity:0.2,stroke:#800080
```

```
admin_level 2级
比例尺:75,0000
stroke-width:6,stroke-opacity:0.1,stroke:#800080
```

```
admin_level 3级
比例尺:75,0000
stroke-width:5,stroke-opacity:0.1,stroke:#800080,dasharray:4 2
```
```
admin_level 4级
比例尺:40,0000 到 650,0000
stroke-width:1,stroke-opacity:0.2,stroke:#800080,dasharray:4 3
```

```
admin_level 4级
比例尺:40,0000
stroke-width:3,stroke-opacity:0.2,stroke:#800080,dasharray:4 3
```







<StyledLayerDescriptor version="1.0.0" xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" xmlns:ogc="http://www.opengis.net/ogc" xmlns="http://www.opengis.net/sld">
<NamedLayer>
<Name>admin-01234</Name>
<UserStyle>
<Name>admin-01234</Name>
<FeatureTypeStyle>
<Rule><Filter xmlns="http://www.opengis.net/ogc"><Or><PropertyIsEqualTo><PropertyName>admin_level</PropertyName><Literal>2</Literal></PropertyIsEqualTo><PropertyIsEqualTo><PropertyName>admin_level</PropertyName><Literal>3</Literal></PropertyIsEqualTo></Or></Filter><MinScaleDenominator>6500000</MinScaleDenominator><MaxScaleDenominator>50000000</MaxScaleDenominator><LineSymbolizer>
<Stroke><CssParameter name="stroke-opacity">0.2</CssParameter><CssParameter name="stroke-width">0.6</CssParameter><CssParameter name="stroke">#800080</CssParameter></Stroke>
</LineSymbolizer>
</Rule>

</LineSymbolizer>

</LineSymbolizer>
</Rule>

<xsd:schema targetNamespace="http://www.opengis.net/se" xmlns:se="http://www.opengis.net/se" xmlns:ogc="http://www.opengis.net/ogc" xmlns:xsd="http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema" elementFormDefault="qualified" version="1.1.0.2">
  <!-- This version of se/1.1.0 was previously versioned as '1.1.1' . -->
	<xsd:include schemaLocation="Symbolizer.xsd"/>

	<!-- *********************************************************************** -->
	<xsd:annotation>
		<xsd:documentation>
      Symbology Encoding FEATURE STYLE version 1.1.0 (2010-02-01)
      
      Symbology Encoding is an OGC Standard.

      To obtain additional rights of use, visit http://www.opengeospatial.org/legal/ .
		</xsd:documentation>

      A FeatureTypeStyle contains styling information specific to one
      feature type.
    </xsd:documentation>
		</xsd:annotation>
	</xsd:element>

				<xsd:element ref="se:OnlineResource"/>
			</xsd:choice>
		</xsd:sequence>

      </xsd:documentation>

	</xsd:complexType>

      </xsd:documentation>
		</xsd:annotation>
	</xsd:element>
